    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Paneer Tikka is a popular Indian appetizer made from marinated paneer cubes grilled or baked to perfection. It's flavorful, smoky, and a vegetarian delight!</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>30 minutes (plus marination)</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>200g paneer (cubed)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup thick curd (yogurt)</li>
        <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp chaat masala</li>
        <li>1 tbsp lemon juice</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>1 tbsp oil</li>
        <li>1 onion and 1 capsicum (cut into cubes)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>In a bowl, mix curd with spices, lemon juice, salt, and oil to form a marinade.</li>
        <li>Add paneer cubes, onion, and capsicum. Mix well and marinate for 30 minutes.</li>
        <li>Thread paneer and veggies alternately on skewers.</li>
        <li>Grill in a preheated oven at 200¬∞C or on a hot pan until charred and cooked evenly.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with mint chutney and lemon wedges.</li>
    </ol>
